Investors on the equity segment of the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) lost N69.2 billion in value at the close of business yesterday as market capitalisation fell to N13.4 trillion. Sell pressures in bellwether stocks such as Dangote Cement (DANGCEM) (-1.2 per cent), Guaranty Trust Bank (GTB) (-1.1 per cent) and Zenith Bank (-1.4 per cent) dragged the benchmark index 52bps lower to close at 27,527.40 points, which has seen Year-To-Date (YTD) loss worsened to -12.4 per cent. Activity level was mixed as volume traded declined 39.2 per cent to 170.7m units, while value traded advanced by 60.5 per cent to N2.3bn. The top traded stocks by volume were Access bank (65.1m units), GTB (17.6m units) and Dangote Flour (DANGFLOUR) (16.2m units), while GTB (N488.8m), Access (N409.2m) and DANGFLOUR (N324.5m) led the top trades by value. Performance across sectors was largely bearish as five of six indices under NSE coverage closed in the red. Stock market near bottom as benchmark index hits 3-year low Stocks close flat as long-term investors expect to take position Equities plunges further by N114bn Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin